***************************** Session-2 CSS*****************************************************
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>CSS Introduction Project</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
      
        <nav>
            <a href="#">Home</a>
            <a href="#">Introduction</a>
            <a href="#">Syntax</a>
            <a href="#">Properties</a>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
        <h1>Introduction to CSS</h1>
        <p>CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets. It is a language used to style and layout web pages. CSS allows you to apply styles to web pages, such as fonts, colors, and spacing, without changing the underlying HTML content.</p>
        <p>Here are some of the benefits of using CSS:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Improved separation of concerns: CSS separates the presentation of a web page from its content, making the code more maintainable.</li>
            <li>Easier to maintain: Changes to the style of a web page can be made in one place (the CSS file) instead of having to modify the HTML code for each page.</li>
            <li>More consistent design: CSS can be used to create a consistent look and feel for a website across all pages.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Basic CSS Syntax</h2>
        <p>A basic CSS rule consists of a selector and a declaration block.</p>
        <pre>
            selector {
                property: value;
            }
        </pre>
        <p>The selector specifies the HTML element(s) that the style rule applies to. The declaration block contains one or more property-value pairs, separated by semicolons. The property specifies the style that you want to change, and the value specifies the new value for that property.</p>

        <h2>Example</h2>
        <p>Let's look at an example of how to use CSS to change the color of all the paragraph elements on a web page.</p>
        <pre>
            p {
                color: red;
            }
        </pre>
        <p>This code will change the color of all the `<p>` elements on the page to red.</p>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 CSS Introduction Project</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>

/* Basic styles */
